# Code Style — {{.ProjectName}}

## TypeScript

- Strict mode always: `strict: true` in tsconfig with no overrides
- Named exports only — no default exports
- Use `type` aliases over `interface` for DTOs and function signatures
- Avoid enums; prefer `as const` objects or string literal unions
- Use `satisfies` for type-safe constant definitions

## File Naming

- **kebab-case** for all files and directories: `user-profile.route.ts`, `auth.middleware.ts`
- Suffix files by layer: `.route.ts`, `.service.ts`, `.repository.ts`, `.middleware.ts`, `.schema.ts`
- One primary export per file; colocate related types in the same file

## Validation

- Zod schemas live alongside the route that uses them (e.g., `user.route.ts` and `user.schema.ts` in the same directory)
- Extract shared schemas (pagination, ID params) to `src/types/schemas/`
- Infer TypeScript types from Zod schemas with `z.infer<typeof schema>` — don't duplicate types manually

## Error Handling

- Throw `AppError` for expected errors (validation failures, not-found, auth failures)
- Let unexpected errors propagate to the global error handler unmodified
- Never return error responses directly from route handlers — always throw and let middleware handle it

## Functions

- Keep functions pure when possible — especially services and utilities
- Dependency injection via constructor parameters, not module-level singletons
- Prefer early returns to reduce nesting
